          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "INTAD"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Neutrons  leaving  Pb-207 in its ground state",
                " and first two excited states were resolved  and  the",
                " angular   distributions   of   these  partial  cross",
                " sections were measured at seven angles  from  45  to",
                " 135  degrees  inclusive.  The partial cross sections",
                " for leaving Pb-207 in its ground state and first two",
                " excited  states  were  derived  by integrating these",
                " differential cross sections.  The total photoneutron",
                " cross  section  was obtained as sum of these partial",
                " cross sections in the energy region studied."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "ERR-S",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The statistical errors."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "ERR-1",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The estimated value of systematic error",
                " associated with absolute photoneutron cross sections",
                " is less than 20%."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The partial differential photoneutron cross  sections",
                " for  Pb-208  were measured in the energy region from",
                " 9.9 to 11.2 MeV with an energy resolution  of  about",
                " 100  keV  using  the beam of tagged photons and then",
                " were used to obtain  the  total  photoneutron  cross",
                " section."
              ]
            }
          ],
